    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sound Porsche 911 Carrera 2 (996.1) featuring the high-revving 3.4L naturally aspirated flat-six. This example is equipped with the desirable 6-speed G96 manual transaxle and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. To ensure long-term reliability, the IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row retrofit, alongside a fresh rear main seal and water pump. The chassis remains taut, utilizing its original MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension to provide exceptional communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. It delivers a raw, analog driving experience with linear power delivery and firm pedal feel from the four-piston monobloc calipers. A well-maintained enthusiast spec ready for the apex.",
